As in other European countries, there is no indication of a severe epidemic though the number of detected influenza viruses is high. It could be presumed that the spreading of the virus is reduced by a natural immunity acquired the previous year against the same strains and by a vaccination coverage that is increasing each year in every country. In 1998, 14% of the whole population was vaccinated against flu in Belgium.
